[[File:120725 Osaka Tenjinmatsuri Japan08bs.jpg|thumb|Tenjin Matsuri. In Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture.]] {{nihongo|'''Tenjin Matsuri'''|天神祭|Tenjin Matsuri}} is a festival held throughout Japan on the 24 and 25 July every year at ''[[Tenmangū]]'' shrines. The festival commemorates the death anniversary of the deity [[Sugawara no Michizane]], of these festivals, the one held in Osaka at [[Osaka Tenmangū|Osaka Tenmangu Shrine]] is the largest. The celebrations climax with a 100 river-boat procession and fireworks show. The reflection of fireworks and lanterns on the Okawa River give it its alternative name of the '''Festival of Fire and Water'''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cheng |first=Andy |date=2021-07-06 |title=Tenjin Matsuri: The Dance of Fire and Water |url=https://www.osaka.com/events/tenjin-matsuri/ |access-date=2024-07-26 |website=Osaka.com |language=en-AU}}</ref>
Along with the [[Kishiwada Danjiri Matsuri|Kishiwada Danjiri]], Tenjin Matsuri is one of the key Shintō festivals of Osaka, and among the most famous in Japan.
== History == The legendary history of the event states that it began in the year 951 AD, two years after the establishment of Osaka's Tenmangu Shrine.{{citation needed|date= July 2024}}
